{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I was informed by this kind of"},{"time":3000,"text":"unoriginal and trite idea"},{"time":5000,"text":"that new technologies were an opportunity"},{"time":7000,"text":"for social transformation,"},{"time":9000,"text":"which is what drove me then,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and still, it's a delusion that drives me now."},{"time":13000,"text":"I wanted to update what I've been doing since then --"},{"time":16000,"text":"but it's still the same theme song --"},{"time":19000,"text":"and introduce you to my lab and current work,"},{"time":22000,"text":"which is the Environmental Health Clinic"},{"time":24000,"text":"that I run at NYU."},{"time":26000,"text":"And what it is -- it's a twist on health."},{"time":28000,"text":"Because, really, what I'm trying to do now"},{"time":30000,"text":"is redefine what counts as health."},{"time":32000,"text":"It's a clinic like a health clinic at any other university,"},{"time":35000,"text":"except people come to the clinic"},{"time":37000,"text":"with environmental health concerns,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and they walk out with prescriptions"},{"time":41000,"text":"for things they can do to improve environmental health,"},{"time":44000,"text":"as opposed to coming to a clinic with medical concerns"},{"time":47000,"text":"and walking out with prescriptions for pharmaceuticals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"It's a handy-dandy quote from Hippocrates of the Hippocratic oath"},{"time":53000,"text":"that says, \"The greater part of the soul lays outside the body,"},{"time":56000,"text":"treatment of the inner requires treatment of the outer.\""},{"time":58000,"text":"But that suggests the issue"},{"time":60000,"text":"that I'm trying to get at here,"},{"time":62000,"text":"that we have an opportunity to redefine what is health."},{"time":65000,"text":"Because this idea that health is internal"},{"time":67000,"text":"and atomized and individual"},{"time":70000,"text":"and pharmaceutical"},{"time":72000,"text":"is largely an error."},{"time":74000,"text":"And I would use this study,"},{"time":76000,"text":"a recent study by Philip Landrigan,"},{"time":78000,"text":"to motivate a different view of health,"},{"time":80000,"text":"where he went to most of the pediatricians in Manhattan"},{"time":83000,"text":"and the New York area"},{"time":85000,"text":"and logged what they spent their patient hours on."},{"time":88000,"text":"80 to 90 percent of their time"},{"time":90000,"text":"was spent on five things."},{"time":92000,"text":"Number one was asthma,"},{"time":94000,"text":"number two was developmental delays,"},{"time":97000,"text":"number three was 400-fold increases"},{"time":99000,"text":"in rare childhood cancers"},{"time":101000,"text":"in the last eight to 10, 15 years."},{"time":104000,"text":"Number four and five were childhood obesity"},{"time":107000,"text":"and diabetes-related issues."},{"time":110000,"text":"So all of those -- what's common about all of those?"},{"time":113000,"text":"The environment is implicated, radically implicated, right."},{"time":116000,"text":"This is not the germs"},{"time":118000,"text":"that medicos were trained to deal with;"},{"time":121000,"text":"this is a different definition of health,"},{"time":124000,"text":"health that has a great advantage"},{"time":127000,"text":"because it's external, it's shared,"},{"time":129000,"text":"we can do something about it,"},{"time":131000,"text":"as opposed to internal, genetically predetermined"},{"time":134000,"text":"or individualized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"People who come to the clinic are called, not patients,"},{"time":138000,"text":"but impatients,"},{"time":140000,"text":"because they're too impatient to wait for legislative change"},{"time":143000,"text":"to address local and environmental health issues."},{"time":146000,"text":"And I meet them at the University, I also have a few field offices"},{"time":149000,"text":"that I set up in various places"},{"time":151000,"text":"that provide an immersion"},{"time":153000,"text":"in some of the environmental challenges we face."},{"time":155000,"text":"I like this one from the Belgian field office,"},{"time":158000,"text":"where we met in a roundabout,"},{"time":160000,"text":"precisely because the roundabout iconified"},{"time":162000,"text":"the headless social movement"},{"time":164000,"text":"that informs much social transformation,"},{"time":167000,"text":"as opposed to the top-down control"},{"time":169000,"text":"of red light traffic intersections."},{"time":172000,"text":"In this case, of course, the roundabout"},{"time":175000,"text":"with that micro-decisions being made in situ"},{"time":177000,"text":"by people not being told what to do."},{"time":180000,"text":"But, of course, affords greater throughput,"},{"time":182000,"text":"fewer accidents,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and an interesting model of social movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"Some of the things that the monitoring protocols have developed:"},{"time":189000,"text":"this is the tadpole bureaucrat protocol,"},{"time":192000,"text":"or keeping tabs, if you will."},{"time":195000,"text":"What they are is an addition of tadpoles"},{"time":197000,"text":"that are named after a local bureaucrat"},{"time":199000,"text":"whose decisions affect your water quality."},{"time":202000,"text":"So an impatient concerned for water quality"},{"time":205000,"text":"would raise a tadpole bureaucrat"},{"time":208000,"text":"in a sample of water in which they're interested."},{"time":211000,"text":"And we give them a couple of things to do that,"},{"time":213000,"text":"to help them do companion animal devices"},{"time":215000,"text":"while they're blogging and doing their email."},{"time":217000,"text":"This is a tadpole walker"},{"time":219000,"text":"to take your tadpole walking in the evening."},{"time":222000,"text":"And the interesting thing that happens --"},{"time":224000,"text":"because we're using tadpoles, of course,"},{"time":226000,"text":"because they have the most exquisite biosenses that we have,"},{"time":229000,"text":"several orders of magnitude more sensitive"},{"time":231000,"text":"than some of our senses"},{"time":233000,"text":"for sensing,"},{"time":236000,"text":"responding in a biologically meaningful way,"},{"time":238000,"text":"to that whole class of industrial contaminants"},{"time":240000,"text":"we call endocrine disruptors"},{"time":242000,"text":"or hormone emulators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"But by taking your tadpole out for a walk in the evening --"},{"time":247000,"text":"there's a few action shots --"},{"time":249000,"text":"your neighbors are likely to say, \"What are you doing?\""},{"time":252000,"text":"And then you have to introduce your tadpole"},{"time":255000,"text":"and who it's named after."},{"time":257000,"text":"You have to explain what you're doing"},{"time":259000,"text":"and how the developmental events of a tadpole"},{"time":261000,"text":"are, of course, very observable"},{"time":263000,"text":"and they use the same T3-mediated hormones that we do."},{"time":268000,"text":"And so next time your neighbor sees you"},{"time":271000,"text":"they'll say, \"How is that tadpole doing?\""},{"time":274000,"text":"And you can let them social network with your tadpole,"},{"time":277000,"text":"because the Environmental Health Clinic has a social networking site"},{"time":280000,"text":"for, not only impatients, humans,"},{"time":283000,"text":"but non-humans,"},{"time":285000,"text":"social networking for humans and non-humans."},{"time":287000,"text":"And of course, these endocrine disruptors"},{"time":289000,"text":"are things that are implicated in the breast cancer epidemic,"},{"time":292000,"text":"the obesity epidemic,"},{"time":294000,"text":"the two and a half year drop in the average age of onset of puberty in young girls"},{"time":297000,"text":"and other related things."},{"time":299000,"text":"The culmination of this is if you've successfully raised your tadpole,"},{"time":302000,"text":"observing the behavioral"},{"time":304000,"text":"and developmental events,"},{"time":306000,"text":"you will then go and introduce your tadpole"},{"time":308000,"text":"to its namesake"},{"time":310000,"text":"and discuss the evidence that you've seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"Another quick protocol -- and I'm going to go through these quickly,"},{"time":316000,"text":"but just to give you the material sense of what we're doing here --"},{"time":319000,"text":"instead of asking you for urine samples,"},{"time":321000,"text":"I'll ask you for a mouse sample."},{"time":323000,"text":"Anyone here lucky enough to share, to cohabit with a mouse --"},{"time":326000,"text":"a domestic partnership with mice?"},{"time":328000,"text":"Very lucky."},{"time":331000,"text":"Mice, of course, are the quintessential"},{"time":334000,"text":"model organism."},{"time":336000,"text":"They're even better models of environmental health,"},{"time":338000,"text":"because not only the same mammalian biology,"},{"time":340000,"text":"but they share your diet, largely."},{"time":342000,"text":"They share your environmental stressors,"},{"time":345000,"text":"the asbestos levels and lead levels,"},{"time":347000,"text":"whatever you're exposed to."},{"time":349000,"text":"And they're geographically more limited than you are,"},{"time":351000,"text":"because we don't know if you've been exposed"},{"time":353000,"text":"to persistent organic pollutants"},{"time":355000,"text":"in your home, or occupationally"},{"time":357000,"text":"or as a child."},{"time":359000,"text":"Mice are a very good representation."},{"time":361000,"text":"So it starts by building a better mousetrap, of course."},{"time":364000,"text":"This is one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"Coping with environmental stressors is tricky."},{"time":368000,"text":"Is anybody here on antidepressants?"},{"time":371000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":373000,"text":"There's a lot of people in Manhattan are."},{"time":376000,"text":"And we were testing if the mice"},{"time":378000,"text":"would also self-administer SSRIs."},{"time":381000,"text":"So this was Prozac, this was Zoloft,"},{"time":383000,"text":"this was a black jellybean and this was muscle relaxant,"},{"time":386000,"text":"all of which were the medications that the impatient was taking."},{"time":389000,"text":"So do you think the mice"},{"time":391000,"text":"self-administered antidepressants?"},{"time":393000,"text":"What's the -- (Audience: Sure. Yes.)"},{"time":396000,"text":"How did you know that? They did."},{"time":399000,"text":"This was vodka and solution, gin and solution."},{"time":401000,"text":"This guy also liked plain water and the muscle relaxant."},{"time":404000,"text":"Where's our expert?"},{"time":406000,"text":"Vodka, gin --"},{"time":408000,"text":"(Audience: [unclear])"},{"time":410000,"text":"Yes. Yes. You know your mice well."},{"time":413000,"text":"They did, yes."},{"time":415000,"text":"So they drank as much vodka as they did plain water,"},{"time":417000,"text":"which was interesting."},{"time":419000,"text":"Then of course, it goes into the entrapment device."},{"time":422000,"text":"There's an old cellphone in there -- a good use for old cellphones --"},{"time":424000,"text":"which dials the clinic, we go and pick up the mouse."},{"time":427000,"text":"We take the blood sample"},{"time":429000,"text":"and do the blood work and hair work on the mice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"And I want to sort of point out the big advantage"},{"time":433000,"text":"of framing health in this external way."},{"time":436000,"text":"But we do have a few prescription products through this."},{"time":439000,"text":"It's very different from the medical model."},{"time":442000,"text":"Anything you do to improve your water quality or air quality,"},{"time":445000,"text":"or to understand it or to change it,"},{"time":448000,"text":"the benefits are enjoyed by anyone"},{"time":450000,"text":"you share that water quality or air quality with."},{"time":453000,"text":"And that aggregating effect,"},{"time":455000,"text":"that collective action effect,"},{"time":458000,"text":"is actually something we can use to our advantage."},{"time":461000,"text":"So I want to show you one prescription product in the clinic"},{"time":464000,"text":"called the No Park."},{"time":466000,"text":"This is a prescription to improve water quality."},{"time":469000,"text":"Many impatients are very concerned for water quality and air quality."},{"time":472000,"text":"What we do is we take a fire hydrant,"},{"time":474000,"text":"a \"no parking\" space associated with a fire hydrant,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and we prescribe the removal of the asphalt"},{"time":480000,"text":"to create an engineered micro landscape,"},{"time":482000,"text":"to create an infiltration opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Because, many of you will know,"},{"time":486000,"text":"that the biggest pollution burden"},{"time":488000,"text":"that we have on the New York, New Jersey harbor right now"},{"time":490000,"text":"is no longer the point sources,"},{"time":492000,"text":"no longer the big polluters,"},{"time":494000,"text":"no longer the GEs,"},{"time":496000,"text":"but that massive network of roads,"},{"time":498000,"text":"[those] impervious surfaces,"},{"time":500000,"text":"that collect all that cadmium neurotoxin that comes from your brake liners"},{"time":503000,"text":"or the oily hydrocarbon waste"},{"time":505000,"text":"in every single storm event and medieval infrastructure"},{"time":508000,"text":"washes it straight into the estuary system."},{"time":510000,"text":"That doesn't do a lot of good."},{"time":512000,"text":"These are little opportunities to intercept those pollutants"},{"time":515000,"text":"before they enter the harbor,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and they're produced by impatients"},{"time":519000,"text":"on various city blocks"},{"time":521000,"text":"in some very interesting ways."},{"time":523000,"text":"I just want to say it was sort of a rule of thumb though,"},{"time":525000,"text":"there's about two or three fire hydrants"},{"time":528000,"text":"on every city block."},{"time":530000,"text":"By creating engineered micro landscapes to infiltrate in them,"},{"time":533000,"text":"we don't prevent them from being used"},{"time":535000,"text":"as emergency vehicle parking spaces,"},{"time":537000,"text":"because, of course, a firetruck can come and park there."},{"time":540000,"text":"They flatten a few plants. No big deal, they'll regenerate."},{"time":544000,"text":"But if we did this"},{"time":546000,"text":"in every single --"},{"time":549000,"text":"every fire hydrant"},{"time":551000,"text":"we could redefine the emergency."},{"time":554000,"text":"That 99 percent of the time"},{"time":556000,"text":"when a firetruck is not parking there,"},{"time":559000,"text":"it's infiltrating pollutants."},{"time":561000,"text":"It's also increasing fixing CO2s,"},{"time":564000,"text":"sequestering some of the airborne pollutants."},{"time":567000,"text":"And aggregated,"},{"time":569000,"text":"these smaller interceptions"},{"time":571000,"text":"could actually infiltrate all the roadborne pollution"},{"time":574000,"text":"that now runs into the estuary system,"},{"time":576000,"text":"up to a seven inch rain event, up to a hundred-year storm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"So these are small actions"},{"time":581000,"text":"that can amount to a significant effect"},{"time":583000,"text":"to improve local environmental health."},{"time":586000,"text":"This is one of the more ambitious ones."},{"time":588000,"text":"What the climate crisis has revealed to us"},{"time":591000,"text":"is a secondary, more insidious"},{"time":593000,"text":"and more pervasive crisis,"},{"time":596000,"text":"which is the crisis of agency,"},{"time":599000,"text":"which is what to do."},{"time":602000,"text":"Somehow buying a local lettuce, changing a light bulb,"},{"time":605000,"text":"driving the speed limit, changing your tires regularly,"},{"time":607000,"text":"doesn't seem sufficient"},{"time":609000,"text":"in the face of climate crisis."},{"time":612000,"text":"And this is an interesting icon that happened --"},{"time":614000,"text":"you remember these: fallout shelters."},{"time":617000,"text":"What is the fallout shelter"},{"time":619000,"text":"for the climate crisis?"},{"time":621000,"text":"This was civic mobilization."},{"time":623000,"text":"Churches, school groups,"},{"time":625000,"text":"hospitals, private residents --"},{"time":627000,"text":"everyone built one of these in a matter of months."},{"time":629000,"text":"And they still remain"},{"time":631000,"text":"as icons of civic response"},{"time":634000,"text":"in the face of shared, uncertain, collective threat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"Fallout shelter for the climate crisis,"},{"time":638000,"text":"I would say, looks something like this, or this,"},{"time":641000,"text":"which is an intensive urban agriculture facility"},{"time":643000,"text":"that's due to go on my lab building at NYU."},{"time":646000,"text":"What it does"},{"time":648000,"text":"is a very simple idea"},{"time":650000,"text":"of taking --"},{"time":652000,"text":"80 to 90 percent of the CO2 produced in Manhattan"},{"time":655000,"text":"is building related --"},{"time":657000,"text":"we take, just like a commercial greenhouse,"},{"time":659000,"text":"we take the CO2 from the building --"},{"time":661000,"text":"CO2-enriched air --"},{"time":663000,"text":"we force it through the urban agriculture facility,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and then we resupply oxygen-enriched air."},{"time":668000,"text":"You can't actually build much on a roof, they're not designed for that."},{"time":671000,"text":"So it's on legs,"},{"time":673000,"text":"so it focuses all the load on the masonry walls and the columns."},{"time":676000,"text":"It's built as a barn raising,"},{"time":678000,"text":"using open source hardware."},{"time":680000,"text":"This is the quarter-scale prototype"},{"time":682000,"text":"that was functioning in Spain."},{"time":684000,"text":"This is what it will look like, fingers crossed,"},{"time":686000,"text":"NYU willing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"And what I want to show you is --"},{"time":690000,"text":"actually this is one of the components of it that we've just recently been testing --"},{"time":693000,"text":"which is a solar chimney --"},{"time":695000,"text":"we have got 17 of them now put around New York at the moment --"},{"time":697000,"text":"that passively draws air up."},{"time":699000,"text":"You understand a solar chimney."},{"time":701000,"text":"Hot air rises."},{"time":703000,"text":"You put a bit of black plastic on the side of a building,"},{"time":705000,"text":"it'll heat up, and you'll get passive airflow."},{"time":708000,"text":"What we do is actually"},{"time":710000,"text":"put a standard HVAC filter on the top of that."},{"time":713000,"text":"That actually removes about 95 percent"},{"time":715000,"text":"of the carbon black,"},{"time":717000,"text":"that stuff that, with ozone,"},{"time":719000,"text":"is responsible for about half of global warming's effects,"},{"time":721000,"text":"because it changes, it settles on the snow,"},{"time":723000,"text":"it changes the reflectors,"},{"time":725000,"text":"it changes"},{"time":727000,"text":"the transmission qualities of the atmosphere."},{"time":730000,"text":"Carbon black is that grime"},{"time":732000,"text":"that otherwise lodges in your pretty pink lungs,"},{"time":734000,"text":"and it's associated with."},{"time":736000,"text":"It's not good stuff, and it's from inefficient combustion,"},{"time":739000,"text":"not from combustion itself."},{"time":741000,"text":"When we put it through our solar chimney,"},{"time":744000,"text":"we remove actually about 95 percent of that."},{"time":747000,"text":"And then I swap it out"},{"time":750000,"text":"with the students"},{"time":752000,"text":"and actually re-release that carbon black."},{"time":754000,"text":"And we make pencils the length of which measures the grime"},{"time":757000,"text":"that we've pulled out of the air."},{"time":759000,"text":"Here's one of them that we have up now."},{"time":761000,"text":"Here's who put them up and who are avid pencil users."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Okay, so I want to show you"},{"time":766000,"text":"just two more interfaces,"},{"time":768000,"text":"because I think one of our big challenges"},{"time":770000,"text":"is re-imagining our relationship to natural systems,"},{"time":773000,"text":"not only through this model"},{"time":776000,"text":"of twisted personalized health,"},{"time":779000,"text":"but through the animals"},{"time":781000,"text":"with whom we cohabit."},{"time":783000,"text":"We are not alone; the animals are moving in."},{"time":785000,"text":"In fact, urban migration now describes"},{"time":787000,"text":"the movement of animals formerly known as wild"},{"time":790000,"text":"into urban centers."},{"time":792000,"text":"You know, coyote in Central Park, a whale in the Gowanus Canal,"},{"time":794000,"text":"elk in Westchester County."},{"time":796000,"text":"It's happening all over the Developed World,"},{"time":798000,"text":"probably for loss of habitat,"},{"time":800000,"text":"but also because our cities are a little bit more livable"},{"time":802000,"text":"than they have been."},{"time":804000,"text":"And every green space we create"},{"time":806000,"text":"is an invitation for non-humans to cohabit with us."},{"time":808000,"text":"But we've kind of lacked imagination"},{"time":810000,"text":"in how we could do that well or interestingly."},{"time":813000,"text":"And I want to show you a few of the technological interfaces"},{"time":815000,"text":"that have been developed under the moniker of OOZ --"},{"time":818000,"text":"which is zoo backwards and without cages --"},{"time":821000,"text":"to try and reform"},{"time":823000,"text":"that relationship."},{"time":825000,"text":"This is communication technology for birds. It looks like this."},{"time":828000,"text":"When a bird lands on it, they trigger a sound file."},{"time":831000,"text":"This is actually in the Whitney Museum, where there were six of them,"},{"time":834000,"text":"each of which had a different argument on it,"},{"time":836000,"text":"different sound file."},{"time":838000,"text":"They said things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"(Whistling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"Recorded Voice: Here's what you need to do."},{"time":845000,"text":"Go down there and buy some of those health food bars,"},{"time":848000,"text":"the ones you call bird food,"},{"time":850000,"text":"and bring it here and scatter it around."},{"time":852000,"text":"There's a good person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855000,"text":"Natalie Jeremijenko: Okay. (Laugher)"},{"time":858000,"text":"So there was several of these."},{"time":860000,"text":"The birds were able to jump from one to the other."},{"time":862000,"text":"These are just your average urban pigeon."},{"time":865000,"text":"And an early test"},{"time":867000,"text":"which argument elicited cooperative behavior"},{"time":869000,"text":"from the people below --"},{"time":872000,"text":"about a hundred to one"},{"time":874000,"text":"decided that this was the argument"},{"time":876000,"text":"that worked best on us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"Recorded Voice: Tick, tick, tick."},{"time":881000,"text":"That's the sound of genetic mutations"},{"time":883000,"text":"of the avian flu"},{"time":885000,"text":"becoming a deadly human flu."},{"time":887000,"text":"Do you know what slows it down?"},{"time":889000,"text":"Healthy sub-populations of birds,"},{"time":891000,"text":"increasing biodiversity generally."},{"time":894000,"text":"It is in your interests that I'm healthy,"},{"time":897000,"text":"happy, well-fed."},{"time":899000,"text":"Hence, you could share some of your nutritional resources"},{"time":902000,"text":"instead of monopolizing them."},{"time":904000,"text":"That is, share your lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"NJ: It worked, and it's true."},{"time":912000,"text":"The final project I'd like to show you"},{"time":914000,"text":"is a new interface for fish"},{"time":916000,"text":"that has just been launched --"},{"time":918000,"text":"it's actually officially launched next week --"},{"time":920000,"text":"with a wonderful commission from the Architectural League."},{"time":922000,"text":"You may not have known that you need to communicate with fish,"},{"time":925000,"text":"but there is now a device for you to do so."},{"time":927000,"text":"It looks like this: buoys that float on the water,"},{"time":930000,"text":"project three foot up, three foot down."},{"time":932000,"text":"When a fish swims underneath, a light goes on."},{"time":935000,"text":"This is what it looks like."},{"time":942000,"text":"So there's another function on here."},{"time":945000,"text":"This top light is -- I'm sorry if I'm making you seasick --"},{"time":949000,"text":"this top light is actually a water quality display"},{"time":951000,"text":"that shifts from red, when the dissolved oxygen is low,"},{"time":954000,"text":"to a blue/green, when its dissolved oxygen is high."},{"time":957000,"text":"And then you can also text the fish."},{"time":960000,"text":"So there's business cards down there"},{"time":962000,"text":"that'll give you contact details."},{"time":964000,"text":"And they text back."},{"time":966000,"text":"When the buoys get your text, they wink at you twice to say, we've got your message."},{"time":969000,"text":"But perhaps the most popular has been"},{"time":971000,"text":"that we've got another array of these boys in the Bronx River,"},{"time":973000,"text":"where the first beaver --"},{"time":975000,"text":"crazy as he is --"},{"time":977000,"text":"to have moved in and built a lodge in New York"},{"time":979000,"text":"in 250 years, hangs out."},{"time":982000,"text":"So updates from a beaver."},{"time":984000,"text":"You can subscribe to updates from him. You can talk to him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"And what I like to think of"},{"time":990000,"text":"is this is an interface"},{"time":993000,"text":"that re-scripts how we interact with natural systems,"},{"time":996000,"text":"specifically by changing who has information,"},{"time":999000,"text":"where they have it,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"who can make sense of that information,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and what you can do about it."},{"time":1005000,"text":"In this case, instead of throwing chewing gum,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"or Doritos or whatever you have in your pocket at the fish --"},{"time":1011000,"text":"There's a body of water in Iceland that I've been dealing with"},{"time":1013000,"text":"that's in the middle of the city,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"and the largest pollution burden on it"},{"time":1017000,"text":"is not the roadborne pollution,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"it's actually white bread"},{"time":1021000,"text":"from people feeding the fish and the birds."},{"time":1023000,"text":"Instead of doing that actually, we've developed some fish sticks"},{"time":1025000,"text":"that you can feed the fish."},{"time":1028000,"text":"They're delicious."},{"time":1030000,"text":"They're cross-species delicious that is,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"delicious for humans and non-humans."},{"time":1035000,"text":"But they also have a chelating agent in them."},{"time":1037000,"text":"They're nutritionally appropriate,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"not like Doritos."},{"time":1041000,"text":"And so every time"},{"time":1044000,"text":"that desire to interact with the animals,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"which is at least as ubiquitous"},{"time":1051000,"text":"as that sign: \"Do not feed the animals.\""},{"time":1053000,"text":"And there's about three of them on every New York City park."},{"time":1056000,"text":"And Yellowstone National Park,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"there's more \"do not feed the animals\" signs"},{"time":1060000,"text":"than there are animals you might wish to feed."},{"time":1063000,"text":"But in that action, that interaction,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"by re-scripting that,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"by changing it into an opportunity"},{"time":1070000,"text":"to offer food that is nutritionally appropriate,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"that could augment the nutritional resources"},{"time":1075000,"text":"that we ourselves have depleted"},{"time":1077000,"text":"for augmenting the fish population"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and also adding chelating agent,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"which, like any chelating agent that we use medicinally,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"binds to the bioaccumulated heavy metals and PCBs"},{"time":1088000,"text":"that are in the fish"},{"time":1090000,"text":"living in this particular habitat"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and allows them to pass it out as a harmless salt"},{"time":1095000,"text":"where it's complexed by a reactive,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"effectively removing it from bioavailability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"But I wanted to say that interaction,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"re-scripting that interaction,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"into collective action, collective remediative action,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"very different from the approach"},{"time":1111000,"text":"that's being used on the other side on the Hudson River,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"where we're dredging the PCBs --"},{"time":1117000,"text":"after 30 years of legislative and legal struggle,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"GE's paying for the dredging"},{"time":1123000,"text":"of the largest Superfund site in the world --"},{"time":1126000,"text":"we're dredging it, and it'll probably get shipped off to Pennsylvania"},{"time":1129000,"text":"or the nearest Third World country,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"where it will continue to be toxic sludge."},{"time":1135000,"text":"Displacement is not the way to deal with environmental issues."},{"time":1139000,"text":"And that's typically the paradigm"},{"time":1141000,"text":"under which we've operated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"By actually taking the opportunity"},{"time":1145000,"text":"that new technologies,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"new interactive technologies, present"},{"time":1149000,"text":"to re-script our interactions,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"to script them,"},{"time":1153000,"text":"not just as isolated, individuated interactions,"},{"time":1156000,"text":"but as collective aggregating actions"},{"time":1160000,"text":"that can amount to something,"},{"time":1162000,"text":"we can really begin to address"},{"time":1164000,"text":"some of our important environmental challenges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1166000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}